1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
 (upbeat music)

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:16,400
 - Good morning, church.

3
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,920
 Good morning, good morning indeed.

4
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:20,920
 Our sermon series is called Make Room.

5
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:23,360
 There's a very crowded, we have a lot of people in here today

6
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:26,260
 so if there is room next to you to make some room,

7
00:00:26,260 --> 00:00:27,160
 could you let us know?

8
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:28,840
 So if you're sitting in the back,

9
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:30,880
 there might be some seats down front,

10
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:32,360
 you can come and join us.

11
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:33,680
 Come on, come on, come on.

12
00:00:33,680 --> 00:00:36,000
 Yes, let's make room for each other.

13
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,720
 All right, well good morning.

14
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:39,680
 If you're joining us online,

15
00:00:39,680 --> 00:00:41,880
 a very good morning to you as well.

16
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:45,520
 Okay, I'm gonna start today with a little Cantonese lesson.

17
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:47,520
 So if you know Cantonese already, that's great.

18
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:49,680
 If you're a local Hong Konger,

19
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:50,600
 but if you don't, okay,

20
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:53,480
 this is a little saying for you today, okay?

21
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:54,600
 It goes like this.

22
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:57,920
 (speaking in foreign language)

23
00:00:57,920 --> 00:01:02,920
 Okay, now, as with many Cantonese idioms and sayings,

24
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:05,840
 the direct translation into English

25
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,880
 doesn't really make much sense, right?

26
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:10,140
 If you directly translate this phrase,

27
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:11,440
 it sounds something like,

28
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:13,440
 why would there be such a big toad

29
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:15,840
 jumping around on the street, okay?

30
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,160
 Like, it doesn't make sense, right?

31
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,680
 Toads jumping around on the street.

32
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,480
 But the meaning behind it,

33
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:23,640
 it's something more along the lines of,

34
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:26,000
 it's too good to be true, right?

35
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,960
 There's no such thing as a free lunch.

36
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,560
 Apparently, maybe once upon a time,

37
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:33,100
 big toads were very desirable, okay, for food or whatever.

38
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:35,920
 So, you know, right, it's too good to be true, right?

39
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,840
 It can't be true.

40
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,120
 It's too wonderful.

41
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:39,760
 It's too good.

42
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:43,120
 And maybe, you know, you've heard news like that,

43
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,600
 you know, like when you hear news

44
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:47,480
 that sounds too good to be true at first, right?

45
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:50,680
 Our initial reaction usually is doubt, right?

46
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,120
 When that doesn't happen.

47
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,680
 No, that's not really gonna happen.

48
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:58,300
 My biggest doubt in life is getting free upgrades, right,

49
00:01:58,300 --> 00:02:01,240
 when I travel, when I fly, okay?

50
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:02,880
 I'm always hoping and praying, Lord,

51
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:04,380
 for that free upgrade, right?

52
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:05,520
 I do all the tactics.

53
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:08,120
 Sometimes I dress up a little bit nicer, okay?

54
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,560
 And then you're really kind

55
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,000
 to the person at the check-in desk.

56
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,640
 Oh, wow, you look lovely today, you know?

57
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:15,600
 It's like, thank you for being so patient with us.

58
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,520
 You know, like, okay.

59
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:18,160
 And then, you know, so at the end, you know,

60
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,800
 as they're about to put in, it's like,

61
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,040
 is there any chance of an upgrade today?

62
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:24,320
 You know, just asking, just wondering, right?

63
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:27,480
 The answer has always, always been no, okay?

64
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,960
 But I hear people's stories, right?

65
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,560
 Then they, like, 45 minutes late to check in, right?

66
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:35,040
 They're all frazzled, you know, their luggage is everywhere.

67
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,840
 You know, they don't have their passports on them.

68
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,640
 And the end, the check-in person is like,

69
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:40,520
 oh, you look really stressed out.

70
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:44,400
 Why don't I upgrade you so you can relax a little bit, right?

71
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,360
 Actually, this happened before me

72
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,920
 in front of my very eyes one time.

73
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:52,080
 So a few years ago, my wife and I had just been on a,

74
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,600
 we were on a mission trip, okay?

75
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,320
 Doing the Lord's work, okay?

76
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:57,200
 And it was hot and sweaty.

77
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,720
 It was a really tough trip.

78
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:01,200
 And we were coming home from Hong Kong, okay?

79
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:04,000
 So as we were checking in to come home,

80
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,360
 I was in charge of, I don't know why I was put in charge.

81
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,960
 Okay, worst person ever to put in charge.

82
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,800
 Anything administrative, right, Dewey?

83
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,740
 Do not trust me with it.

84
00:03:10,740 --> 00:03:12,200
 But at that moment, they did.

85
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,840
 And I was distributing out the boarding passes.

86
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:18,000
 And I noticed everyone's number was super low, right?

87
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,040
 Like, single digits.

88
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:22,600
 One B, three A, six D, stuff like that, right?

89
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,240
 I was like, oh, okay, I think we got upgraded.

90
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,760
 Apart from mine, okay?

91
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:29,800
 I was in 11 B, okay, 11 B.

92
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,720
 So I was handing out the boarding passes

93
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:33,600
 and then I said to my wife,

94
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:36,180
 I think everyone in the group, in the team,

95
00:03:36,180 --> 00:03:38,080
 got upgraded apart from me.

96
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,280
 She's like, oh no, surely not.

97
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,560
 You know, they checked us in together.

98
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,400
 You'll be fine.

99
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,680
 And then she said this, right?

100
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:46,320
 Even if that happens, I'll come sit with you instead.

101
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:47,640
 It's like, oh, so sweet.

102
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:49,840
 Well, we were newlywed at that time, okay?

103
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:54,520
 So, and so we get on the plane, right?

104
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:57,160
 And sure enough, okay, as we're going on,

105
00:03:57,160 --> 00:04:00,080
 they were like, okay, Mr. Bennett, yes, to the left, right?

106
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:02,080
 Oh, Mr. Tsang, to the left.

107
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:04,980
 Now, to the left is a good thing in planes,

108
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:06,120
 not in Beyonce songs, right?

109
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,720
 But on the airplane, okay, to the left is a good thing

110
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,720
 'cause that's where the upper classes are, right?

111
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:12,600
 The upper cabin classes, right?

112
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,240
 And so, you know, they all went to the left

113
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,680
 and when, sure enough, when they got to me,

114
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:18,640
 they were like, okay, sir, you sit right here, okay?

115
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:21,640
 I was in the very first row of the business class, right?

116
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:24,760
 Next to the toilet and the curtain, okay?

117
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:27,880
 With a screaming child next to me, right?

118
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:30,040
 You saw what happened to my wife, okay?

119
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,640
 She dropped me like a bad habit.

120
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:34,600
 The moment she went left and they handed her a cocktail,

121
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,880
 said, oh, Mr. Tsang, here's a mango cocktail

122
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:39,960
 or whatever it was, and she forgot about me totally, okay?

123
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:42,920
 Gone, I didn't see her for the rest of the flight, okay?

124
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:46,400
 You know, and so, you know, this is why, you know,

125
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:49,680
 like, I doubt, right, do good things really happen?

126
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,920
 Maybe not, okay?

127
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:54,720
 Now, it's just a funny illustration to start my point,

128
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:57,040
 but doubt is this thing, right?

129
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:01,480
 Doubt is a very natural part of our humanity, right?

130
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:04,520
 And in some ways, doubt is a good thing, right?

131
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:09,520
 We can't just believe what everyone says all the time, right?

132
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:12,560
 When we hear lies, when we hear things that are not true,

133
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:16,960
 when we see misrepresentations of facts and reality,

134
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:19,200
 not only should we doubt these things,

135
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:22,520
 but our doubt actually gives us a voice to speak out, right,

136
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:26,520
 and shed light into injustice and darkness and untruths

137
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:29,080
 that are being happened around us.

138
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:32,880
 But what happens when our doubt begins

139
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:35,280
 to enter our relationship with God?

140
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:39,920
 And this might be something we all struggle with, too.

141
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:43,000
 At some point in our walk with Jesus,

142
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,240
 we have doubted His goodness, we have doubted His love,

143
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:51,240
 we have doubted His power, and how He can relate to us,

144
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:55,840
 right, especially when we see tragedies unfold before us,

145
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:57,400
 as we've seen in our city.

146
00:05:57,400 --> 00:06:01,240
 It only makes sense that we ask ourselves the question,

147
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:04,080
 right, where is God in all of this?

148
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:06,880
 How could such a loving, powerful God

149
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:09,520
 allow for something like this to happen?

150
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:13,000
 Right, these are questions, very real questions

151
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,220
 we as a whole city are wrestling with right now.

152
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:19,080
 Right, two weeks ago during the fire,

153
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:22,520
 I'm sure I and many of others of you prayed, right?

154
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:25,960
 I remember specifically praying for act of God.

155
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:27,800
 I remember praying, God, just,

156
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:30,720
 I know it's the driest day of the year so far right now,

157
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,880
 but just somehow form a rain cloud

158
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,920
 over the buildings right now

159
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,440
 and just pour down your rain on it

160
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:38,480
 so we can put out these fires and we can see lives get saved.

161
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,640
 But that doesn't happen.

162
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:44,800
 Right, and here, two weeks, three weeks later,

163
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,280
 we're sifting through the damage,

164
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:49,720
 reeling in the pain and grief and mourning

165
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,680
 of what's happened in our city.

166
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:57,000
 And when we sit in the aftermath of a tragedy,

167
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:01,440
 of a disaster, it's very easy for doubt to set in.

168
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:05,120
 So the question we wanna answer today is this,

169
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:07,760
 how do we deal with doubt?

170
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,960
 Because when it's unresolved,

171
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:15,960
 doubt can drive us to a place of despair and hopelessness.

172
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,440
 When we give in to doubt,

173
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:20,880
 it drives a wedge between us and God.

174
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:24,400
 When we begin to doubt God's love for us

175
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,840
 so we no longer want to draw near to him,

176
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:29,960
 we begin to doubt God's plan for us and purposes for us

177
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:32,120
 so we don't trust him anymore.

178
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,960
 When we begin to question God's goodness and kindness,

179
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:38,520
 we close our hearts and leave no room for him

180
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:40,640
 to do his work in our lives.

181
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,760
 And actually, the enemy knows this well.

182
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:47,720
 Doubt is one of the first things the enemy uses

183
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:50,360
 to put distance between us and God.

184
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:53,720
 Right at the very beginning, that was his strategy,

185
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:56,160
 to make Eve doubt the goodness of God

186
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:59,320
 and cause her to sin by trusting herself

187
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,420
 instead of trusting what God had told her.

188
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:06,440
 Eve begins to put doubt on the throne of her heart

189
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:08,000
 instead of God.

190
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,360
 He comes to her with these tricky questions,

191
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:14,120
 saying stuff like, did God really say

192
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:17,120
 you must not eat from any tree in the garden?

193
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:19,800
 You will not surely die.

194
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:22,380
 Come on, Eve, just think about it for a minute, right?

195
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:24,680
 Maybe what God's saying is not true.

196
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,800
 Maybe you should trust in yourself.

197
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:30,160
 And it was these lies of the Satan,

198
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,560
 these lies of the enemy,

199
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:34,760
 that caused humanity to doubt God's commands,

200
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,320
 his ways, his love.

201
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:41,200
 And the consequence of that was sin entering into the world.

202
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:45,960
 When doubt sits on the throne of our hearts,

203
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:49,440
 it blinds us to the goodness of God.

204
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:53,220
 And what we want to do is to take doubt off the throne

205
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:54,920
 and wrestle with it head on,

206
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:57,520
 because actually, if we take doubt

207
00:08:57,520 --> 00:09:01,520
 and use it in the correct way,

208
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:03,740
 it can actually be used for good.

209
00:09:03,740 --> 00:09:07,520
 And I think it's that through doubt

210
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:10,240
 that we can better understand the realities of sin

211
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:12,840
 and brokenness in this world and in our lives,

212
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:17,000
 and draw us closer to God,

213
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,840
 draw us closer to the truth.

214
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:24,960
 The late leader and pastor, Tim Keller, says it this way.

215
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:27,600
 A faith without some doubt is like a human body

216
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:30,120
 without any antibodies.

217
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:32,160
 People who blithely go through life,

218
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:34,900
 too busy or indifferent to ask hard questions

219
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:36,860
 about why they believe as they do,

220
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:39,240
 will find themselves defenseless

221
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:41,720
 against either the experience of tragedy

222
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,920
 or the questions of skeptics.

223
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:48,420
 Believers should acknowledge and wrestle with doubts,

224
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:52,440
 because this is the kind of doubt that helps us see

225
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:56,040
 that even through things we might not understand,

226
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,760
 God is still in control.

227
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,880
 He knows what he's doing.

228
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,840
 He still cares, he still loves,

229
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,640
 and even though we might doubt it at times,

230
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:10,120
 the truth is that with God, all things are still possible.

231
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:13,960
 And so as we step into week two of Advent

232
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:16,240
 and look at the person of Zechariah,

233
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:19,600
 this is the story we see being played out.

234
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:23,000
 A faithful man of God wrestling with doubt,

235
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,720
 holding on in the end to God's promises

236
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:28,720
 until they come through in the end.

237
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:32,040
 So let's turn to the scriptures and see what it says.

238
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,280
 We're in the book of Luke,

239
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:35,840
 as the lady so beautifully read just now,

240
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:38,000
 chapter one, verse five.

241
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,720
 It says this.

242
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:44,640
 In the time of Herod, king of Judea,

243
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,720
 there was a priest named Zechariah

244
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:50,160
 who belonged to the priestly division of Abijah.

245
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:53,820
 His wife Elizabeth was also a descendant of Aaron.

246
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:56,480
 Both of them were righteous in the sight of God,

247
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,120
 observing all the Lord's commands

248
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:00,080
 and decreased blamelessly.

249
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:02,720
 But they were childless

250
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,400
 because Elizabeth was not able to conceive

251
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:08,100
 and they were both very old.

252
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:14,320
 So Luke describes what the very first Christmas was like.

253
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,280
 He starts his gospel by describing to us

254
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,220
 the very first Christmas.

255
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:21,960
 Now, in our modern portrayal of Christmas,

256
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,880
 it's always very festive.

257
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,600
 Looks very warm and inviting.

258
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:26,560
 We look around us, right?

259
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,840
 The team have done a beautiful job

260
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:30,940
 decorating the whole building, right?

261
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,160
 Today we have the market outside.

262
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,600
 It's very warm and inviting.

263
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,440
 We have the bake sale.

264
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,680
 We have mulled wine next week.

265
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:38,240
 All this kind of stuff, right?

266
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,840
 You go down to the malls, IFC, Pacific Place.

267
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,920
 It's all like that, right?

268
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:45,520
 Trees, decorations, cookies, mulled wine, turkey,

269
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,440
 kisses under the mistletoe,

270
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:50,400
 all this really lovely stuff, right?

271
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,880
 And so it's easy for us to think

272
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,720
 that Christmas is always associated

273
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:57,400
 with like warm, fuzzy, jolly things.

274
00:11:57,400 --> 00:12:00,440
 But we're reminded in the gospels

275
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:04,400
 that the first Christmas was far from this.

276
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,520
 And in fact, God's plan of redemption

277
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:08,720
 when Jesus first came into the world

278
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:13,160
 starts with a backdrop of doubt, of pain,

279
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:16,200
 of the people crying out for rescue, right?

280
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:19,120
 For over 400 years, the Israelites

281
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:23,240
 were crying out to the Lord, crying out for rescue,

282
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:26,840
 waiting for this so-called promised Messiah

283
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:30,200
 to come and rescue them from the oppressors.

284
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:33,080
 But things just go from bad to worse, right?

285
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,380
 They start with the Assyrians,

286
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:35,920
 and it goes on to the Babylonians,

287
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:37,520
 and the Persians, and the Greeks,

288
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,920
 and now the Romans.

289
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:41,920
 All these foreign forces have been ruling

290
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:45,680
 over their country.

291
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:48,220
 And they've been waiting for someone

292
00:12:48,220 --> 00:12:51,040
 to come and restore the kingdom.

293
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:54,640
 But instead, at the turn of time and time again,

294
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:57,540
 instead of rescue, just comes more oppression.

295
00:12:57,540 --> 00:13:00,640
 And as Andrew pointed out to us last week,

296
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:03,700
 this latest ruler they have in this little place in Judea

297
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:06,160
 was a man called Herod, right?

298
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,880
 A self-proclaimed king of the Jews, right?

299
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:11,520
 A cruel man who seemed to have no problem

300
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:14,860
 ordering the execution of innocent babies.

301
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:19,120
 Now, that doesn't make for good decorations.

302
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,800
 Like could you imagine a specific place right now

303
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:24,640
 doing a meet King Herod instead of meet Father Christmas?

304
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:28,360
 Hong Kong's mom Facebook group would go absolutely crazy.

305
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:30,200
 That's not the kind of stuff, it's not inviting,

306
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,420
 it's not warm, right?

307
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:33,320
 It's dark, it's real.

308
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:37,160
 It deals with some of the really bad things

309
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:39,060
 that are happening around us.

310
00:13:39,060 --> 00:13:41,560
 And after waiting for so long,

311
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:45,480
 I suspect many had already given in to the doubt.

312
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:47,380
 And maybe they already said that, you know what?

313
00:13:47,380 --> 00:13:48,960
 It's not gonna happen.

314
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:51,640
 God's promises aren't gonna come through.

315
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,620
 The Messiah is not coming.

316
00:13:53,620 --> 00:13:57,720
 And it's in the midst of this doubt

317
00:13:57,720 --> 00:14:01,720
 that we find Zechariah and her husband,

318
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:04,740
 and his wife, right?

319
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:07,640
 An elderly couple who have been faithfully serving God

320
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,480
 for many years, right?

321
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:11,600
 Zechariah was one of the priests

322
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,620
 who was serving the Lord in the temple,

323
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,660
 leading the people in worship.

324
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:19,220
 And Elizabeth, also from a strong Jewish priestly family,

325
00:14:19,220 --> 00:14:21,900
 all the way from one of the descendants of Aarod, right?

326
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:24,900
 Who was with Moses, leading the people of Israel

327
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,780
 out of Egypt.

328
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:29,540
 And so basically, you can think of Zechariah and Elizabeth

329
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:33,180
 like the ultimate pastoral power couple of the time, right?

330
00:14:33,180 --> 00:14:35,860
 Solid background, they say they were righteous

331
00:14:35,860 --> 00:14:40,340
 in the sight of God, observing all of the Lord's commands,

332
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:42,020
 and decreased blamelessly.

333
00:14:42,020 --> 00:14:44,080
 There's not very many people in the Bible

334
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:47,680
 that it describes as being blameless.

335
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:51,060
 But here are these two, blameless before the Lord.

336
00:14:51,060 --> 00:14:54,980
 But even though they were doing all the right things,

337
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:57,420
 even though they were blameless and righteous,

338
00:14:57,420 --> 00:14:59,460
 even though they had been serving God faithfully

339
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:02,520
 all these years, there was a dark cloud

340
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:05,300
 that was hanging over their lives and their marriage, right?

341
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:07,900
 A shadow of doubt, you could say, that followed them.

342
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:11,580
 Scripture tells us they were childless.

343
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:16,520
 Now in those days, childlessness was a symbol of shame

344
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,500
 or even disgrace, right?

345
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,600
 People would have looked, people in the community

346
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,920
 would have looked at Zechariah and Elizabeth

347
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:25,480
 and seen them as maybe being cursed

348
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,420
 or being punished by God.

349
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:31,640
 Now Luke makes it very clear that this was not the case,

350
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,840
 right, because they were blameless, they were righteous.

351
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:37,640
 He goes out of his way to tell us about their character,

352
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:40,800
 right, so their barrenness was not a punishment

353
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:43,500
 or a curse from the Lord.

354
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:47,080
 But it reminds us of this, though,

355
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:51,200
 that faithful service to God does not always mean

356
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,240
 living in God's blessings.

357
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:57,780
 We have to remember that, that obeying God's commands

358
00:15:57,780 --> 00:16:00,600
 doesn't always mean that every single prayer of us

359
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,040
 will be answered, that we were gonna live

360
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:07,040
 these happy, blissful lives all the days of our life.

361
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:10,600
 And like the nation of Israel that had been waiting

362
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:13,600
 400 years, Zechariah and Elizabeth had probably

363
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:17,040
 also given up hope of ever having children of their own.

364
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:21,360
 They were old now, the chance was gone.

365
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:24,560
 And I'm sure they nursed this sense of longing

366
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:26,600
 and emptiness in their hearts,

367
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:31,080
 a dream of being a parent that had slowly faded away

368
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,620
 as the years went by.

369
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:37,840
 But notice this, they did not let the doubt

370
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:40,620
 stop them from serving God with their lives.

371
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:44,480
 Despite the disappointment and their living

372
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:47,440
 in the reality of unanswered prayer,

373
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:52,140
 they remained obedient and devoted to their duty.

374
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:55,800
 And for those of us listening today,

375
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:59,360
 maybe you too have been serving God,

376
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:04,120
 trying your hardest to be obedient and dutiful to Jesus,

377
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:06,520
 but also like this couple, like Zechariah and Elizabeth,

378
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:09,720
 you're living with a sense of disappointment.

379
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:13,800
 You're walking in the reality of unanswered prayer,

380
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:16,240
 a dream that has fizzled out over the years

381
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:18,200
 and because you've been waiting for so long,

382
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,800
 the doubt is starting to set in.

383
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:22,840
 Is God ever gonna come through?

384
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:28,680
 My encouragement for us today in that is this,

385
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:34,680
 hold on, hold on to the Lord because at any moment,

386
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:37,360
 the power of God is gonna break through,

387
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:39,740
 through your doubts, through your pain,

388
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:41,960
 through your disappointment.

389
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:44,800
 And this is what Zechariah is about to experience.

390
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:47,440
 Let's carry on in the story in scripture

391
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,680
 to see what it tells us.

392
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:52,920
 Once, and this is verse eight,

393
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:55,640
 once when Zechariah's division was on duty,

394
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:58,400
 he was serving as the priest before God.

395
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:01,280
 He was chosen by Lot according to the custom

396
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:03,800
 of the priesthood to go into the temple of the Lord

397
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:05,120
 and burn incense.

398
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:07,720
 And when the time for the burning of incense came,

399
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:11,320
 all the assembled worshipers were praying outside.

400
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:15,480
 So like I said just now, Zechariah's job was a priest.

401
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:18,160
 He was one of 18 to 20,000 priests

402
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:21,120
 who would service the temple, right?

403
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:23,760
 And these priests were divided into teams or divisions,

404
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:25,440
 24 different divisions.

405
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:27,840
 These divisions will alternate

406
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,160
 with their duties in the temple.

407
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,680
 So every couple of times a year,

408
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:33,400
 they would go in and serve the temple.

409
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:36,960
 And one of the duties was to offer up the incense.

410
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:39,520
 And the custom was, as I said, right, they cast lots.

411
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:40,360
 I'm not really sure,

412
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:42,560
 maybe it's like bones or dice or something like that, right?

413
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:46,360
 They would cast lots to see who would go in

414
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:49,720
 and do this job of offering up the incense.

415
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:52,400
 Now this was offering up the incense in the inner part,

416
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,720
 okay, into the holy place.

417
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:55,520
 Not quite the holy of holies,

418
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:57,440
 but further into the temple, right?

419
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,560
 And it was a big deal, a big honor.

420
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:03,720
 It was a big deal, a once in a lifetime opportunity.

421
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,040
 And so on the surface, right,

422
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:08,520
 it seems as though this was business as usual.

423
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:09,800
 This is the way we do things.

424
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,120
 Every time it's our turn, we cast lots,

425
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,300
 someone gets chosen to go into the temple,

426
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:17,680
 we offer up incense, and then we keep doing our duties.

427
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:21,320
 But make no mistake, church,

428
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:23,920
 this entire moment, all that's leading up

429
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:26,920
 has all been orchestrated by God, right?

430
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:28,960
 Because this is how God works in the background

431
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:31,040
 of our lives without us knowing.

432
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:32,600
 It might have looked like Zechariah

433
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:35,940
 was just happened to be chosen by lots at that time,

434
00:19:35,940 --> 00:19:40,740
 but the reality was it was God choosing him for this moment.

435
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:42,000
 And he might not know it yet,

436
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:45,360
 but Zechariah, as he goes in to offer up the incense,

437
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:49,740
 his entire reality, his entire life is about to change.

438
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:54,320
 And this is how God often works in our lives.

439
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:55,480
 This is what we mean just now.

440
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:58,820
 When we were singing that song, he doesn't stop working.

441
00:19:58,820 --> 00:20:03,580
 Subtly, quietly, without us being aware,

442
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:07,520
 he's orchestrating things for us.

443
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:11,000
 Because our God is a God who knows,

444
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:16,000
 who sees, who cares, and he works in ways

445
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,800
 that are far better than what we could

446
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,340
 ever come up with ourselves.

447
00:20:19,340 --> 00:20:23,080
 Maybe this is something you have experienced

448
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:25,000
 in your own life, right?

449
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,440
 You've been in the middle of a struggle,

450
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:29,060
 and when you're going through that time of darkness

451
00:20:29,060 --> 00:20:33,060
 and doubt and struggle, it's hard to see what God was doing.

452
00:20:33,060 --> 00:20:36,160
 But it's only when you look back sometimes

453
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:38,340
 that you've seen God's faithfulness at work

454
00:20:38,340 --> 00:20:40,740
 each and every single part of the way

455
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,760
 until you get the full picture.

456
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:45,980
 And this is what scripture is leading us to.

457
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:47,940
 Look at what happens next in the story.

458
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:51,300
 An angel of the Lord then appeared to him,

459
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:53,880
 this is Zechariah, standing on the right side

460
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,780
 of the altar of incense.

461
00:20:55,780 --> 00:20:58,220
 When Zechariah saw him, he was startled

462
00:20:58,220 --> 00:21:00,380
 and was gripped with fear.

463
00:21:00,380 --> 00:21:03,780
 But the angel said to him, "Do not be afraid, Zechariah.

464
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:05,700
 "Your prayer has been answered.

465
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,820
 "Your wife, Elizabeth, will bear you a son,

466
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:09,780
 "and you are to call him John.

467
00:21:09,780 --> 00:21:11,580
 "He will be a joy and delight to you,

468
00:21:11,580 --> 00:21:14,140
 "and many will rejoice because of his birth,

469
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:16,920
 "for he will be great in the sight of the Lord.

470
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:19,420
 "He is never to take wine or the fermented drink,

471
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:21,500
 "and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit

472
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,860
 "even before he is born.

473
00:21:23,860 --> 00:21:28,860
 "He will bring back many of the people of Israel

474
00:21:28,860 --> 00:21:33,140
 "to the Lord their God, and he will go on before the Lord

475
00:21:33,140 --> 00:21:35,580
 "in the spirit and power of Elijah

476
00:21:35,580 --> 00:21:38,140
 "to turn the hearts of the parents to their children

477
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:41,440
 "and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous,

478
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:45,240
 "and to make ready a people prepared for the Lord."

479
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:49,040
 Now, every time I read about angelic encounters

480
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,460
 in scripture, something that always bugs me

481
00:21:51,460 --> 00:21:55,140
 is that I don't feel like angels are very empathetic

482
00:21:55,140 --> 00:21:57,500
 to human beings, okay?

483
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,960
 A bit dismissive about our emotions, right?

484
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:01,860
 Because it's like when they say,

485
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:03,900
 when your wife is angry, never say,

486
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:05,220
 "Hey, just calm down," right?

487
00:22:05,220 --> 00:22:06,340
 That's not helpful.

488
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:08,940
 That was one of the first pieces of advice I get, right?

489
00:22:08,940 --> 00:22:10,900
 This is what I feel like angels are doing

490
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:13,020
 when they say, "Do not be afraid," right?

491
00:22:13,020 --> 00:22:15,900
 Like, sir, literally, this is the most fearful moment

492
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:16,740
 of my life.

493
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:18,140
 I've never seen anything like this.

494
00:22:18,140 --> 00:22:19,460
 Whoever knows what it looks like,

495
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:21,220
 this bright light or whatever, right?

496
00:22:21,220 --> 00:22:23,420
 If an angel suddenly appeared to me,

497
00:22:23,420 --> 00:22:27,740
 I would think my life was coming to an end, right?

498
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:29,940
 Although, just do not be afraid, okay?

499
00:22:29,940 --> 00:22:32,780
 But there is no reason to be afraid for Zechariah

500
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:34,100
 because what, look what he says.

501
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:38,080
 "I bring you good news."

502
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,540
 Good news, Zechariah.

503
00:22:39,540 --> 00:22:41,300
 Your prayer has been heard.

504
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:43,780
 Your wife, Elizabeth, will bear you a son,

505
00:22:43,780 --> 00:22:46,740
 and you are to call him John, right?

506
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:48,820
 Specific, this is actually gonna happen, right?

507
00:22:48,820 --> 00:22:50,020
 You're gonna have a son.

508
00:22:50,020 --> 00:22:52,580
 He's even given a name already.

509
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:55,660
 So all these years of praying and worshiping

510
00:22:55,660 --> 00:22:58,960
 and wondering if God had ever taken notice of their prayers,

511
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:01,740
 they had finally been heard.

512
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:04,820
 Like I said, this was part of God's plan the whole time,

513
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:07,220
 right, in case you need more evidence, check this out.

514
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:10,180
 Zechariah's name, do you know what his name means?

515
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:13,740
 Zechariah's name means God remembers.

516
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:17,580
 The name John, do you know what the name John means?

517
00:23:17,580 --> 00:23:22,580
 John, the name John means God is gracious.

518
00:23:22,580 --> 00:23:27,420
 God had not forgotten the many years of faithful prayer

519
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:29,740
 of Zechariah and Elizabeth,

520
00:23:29,740 --> 00:23:33,480
 and now he was gonna be gracious enough to answer them.

521
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:36,940
 Think about it this way.

522
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:40,180
 The almighty God who controls the entire universe

523
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:43,440
 in his hands, who sees and hears every single cry

524
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:46,500
 of the whole world, who puts the planets into orbit,

525
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:49,300
 who knows exactly the seasons and what's gonna happen,

526
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:53,180
 who's in charge of the entire universe,

527
00:23:53,180 --> 00:23:57,320
 would hear the prayers of a lowly, childless couple.

528
00:23:57,320 --> 00:24:00,900
 I was thinking about this on the bus ride

529
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:02,660
 on the way here this morning, right,

530
00:24:02,660 --> 00:24:04,860
 'cause as I was thinking back through a message,

531
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:08,260
 who am I that the Lord thinks about me?

532
00:24:08,260 --> 00:24:13,100
 That amongst every single person in this world,

533
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:16,380
 he knows me, that he's listening to me right now,

534
00:24:16,380 --> 00:24:19,200
 as I was praying to him this morning.

535
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:22,580
 He knows.

536
00:24:22,580 --> 00:24:24,880
 And what about you?

537
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:28,580
 Maybe you have seen the results of long

538
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:31,280
 and faithful prayer come to pass.

539
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:34,360
 I was with a brother this morning who just told me

540
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,660
 that I've been praying with him for the past year

541
00:24:36,660 --> 00:24:39,240
 about something that he's been wrestling with in his life,

542
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:42,000
 and God finally came through for him.

543
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:45,300
 And one of the biggest answers to prayer I've seen

544
00:24:45,300 --> 00:24:48,180
 in my life happened to a good friend of mine.

545
00:24:48,180 --> 00:24:49,180
 And this friend of mine and I,

546
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:51,740
 we met in Hong Kong as young teens.

547
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:55,740
 He arrived in Hong Kong as a victim of human trafficking.

548
00:24:55,740 --> 00:24:57,940
 Once he was brought to Hong Kong,

549
00:24:57,940 --> 00:25:00,100
 the person that brought him was asking him

550
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:02,020
 to do illegal activities, and he said,

551
00:25:02,020 --> 00:25:03,100
 "I'm not gonna do that."

552
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:05,660
 And so he took everything he had,

553
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:07,680
 all the money, all his passports, everything,

554
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:09,860
 and just abandoned him at the Star Ferry Pier

555
00:25:09,860 --> 00:25:11,460
 in Tsim Sha Tsui.

556
00:25:11,460 --> 00:25:14,500
 And at the church I was with at the time,

557
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:17,100
 one of our members found him and brought him to church,

558
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:17,940
 and that's where we met,

559
00:25:17,940 --> 00:25:20,100
 that's where we became good friends.

560
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:23,860
 But as an asylum seeker in Hong Kong,

561
00:25:23,860 --> 00:25:27,540
 as many of us know, you are very vulnerable.

562
00:25:27,540 --> 00:25:29,680
 And so one day he found himself being locked up

563
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,840
 in a detention center.

564
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:34,700
 He was just a, he's still a young man at this point,

565
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:36,460
 in his mid-teens.

566
00:25:36,460 --> 00:25:39,940
 And whilst he was there, he decided that one day,

567
00:25:39,940 --> 00:25:44,420
 when I'm gonna be released, I want to go back to school.

568
00:25:44,420 --> 00:25:48,580
 And so every day he began praying and writing letters

569
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:50,860
 to the director of immigration,

570
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:53,380
 asking to be released so that he could have a chance

571
00:25:53,380 --> 00:25:57,540
 to resume a bit of normal life, go back to school,

572
00:25:57,540 --> 00:25:59,140
 and keep learning again.

573
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:00,700
 And so for 10 months he was detained,

574
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,680
 and he dreamed every day of those 10 months,

575
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:05,380
 writing letters, praying, we were praying for him,

576
00:26:05,380 --> 00:26:07,420
 I would go and visit, we would pray together,

577
00:26:07,420 --> 00:26:11,060
 writing letters, but never got a response.

578
00:26:11,060 --> 00:26:12,980
 And so one day he was summoned

579
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:15,260
 by the director of immigration.

580
00:26:15,260 --> 00:26:17,540
 Now, normally that's not a good sign.

581
00:26:17,540 --> 00:26:20,820
 Normally that means if you get summoned by the director,

582
00:26:20,820 --> 00:26:22,720
 they reviewed your case, case closed,

583
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:25,180
 we're gonna send you back to where you came from.

584
00:26:25,180 --> 00:26:28,540
 But he walks into the director's office,

585
00:26:28,540 --> 00:26:32,260
 and he sees the stack of letters that he's written.

586
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:33,260
 And the director told him,

587
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:36,620
 so apparently you want to go to school, right?

588
00:26:36,620 --> 00:26:38,500
 And he said, yes, I really do.

589
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:41,680
 And so he said, okay, we've made a decision.

590
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:44,860
 Once you get released, you can stay in Hong Kong,

591
00:26:44,860 --> 00:26:47,300
 and you can go back to school, right?

592
00:26:47,300 --> 00:26:48,380
 And so amazing, right?

593
00:26:48,380 --> 00:26:50,380
 We celebrated so much, right?

594
00:26:50,380 --> 00:26:53,220
 These long answer prayers, I remember when he came out,

595
00:26:53,220 --> 00:26:54,300
 he had to start at the beginning,

596
00:26:54,300 --> 00:26:56,980
 so he started in K3 or P1,

597
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:59,740
 so it was like, went to his, I'm not joking,

598
00:26:59,740 --> 00:27:01,240
 a kindergarten graduation, right?

599
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:02,940
 Like, these little kids, right?

600
00:27:02,940 --> 00:27:04,060
 And then my friends, okay?

601
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:06,220
 And then like, these little kids again.

602
00:27:06,220 --> 00:27:08,940
 Okay, but then he went on, finished primary school,

603
00:27:08,940 --> 00:27:12,000
 finished high school, went on to get a university degree,

604
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:14,200
 went on to get a postgraduate degree, right?

605
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:16,440
 Marry his wife, and now, thankfully,

606
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:18,300
 he's no longer in Hong Kong.

607
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:21,660
 He's gone abroad and made a new life for himself.

608
00:27:21,660 --> 00:27:23,200
 Right, praise the Lord, amen.

609
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,040
 You can clap for that.

610
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:27,200
 [audience applauding]

611
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:32,980
 No situation in life is too small or insignificant

612
00:27:32,980 --> 00:27:35,220
 for God to notice when we pray to Him.

613
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:39,340
 Like I said, Elizabeth and Zachariah,

614
00:27:39,340 --> 00:27:44,340
 just a normal couple praying faithfully for a child.

615
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:46,420
 My friend, a young lost boy,

616
00:27:46,420 --> 00:27:48,780
 praying of an opportunity for school.

617
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:52,500
 And whatever your prayer request is

618
00:27:52,500 --> 00:27:55,200
 that you bring before the Lord as well.

619
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:57,420
 In the grand scheme of things,

620
00:27:57,420 --> 00:27:58,740
 or in the eyes of the world,

621
00:27:58,740 --> 00:28:01,140
 maybe these poor people weren't very important,

622
00:28:01,140 --> 00:28:06,400
 but God sees it all, and God hears it all.

623
00:28:06,820 --> 00:28:09,900
 And He walks with us through those times of prayer.

624
00:28:09,900 --> 00:28:16,820
 But there's something even more amazing happening here.

625
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:19,820
 You see, often when we get stuck in doubt, right,

626
00:28:19,820 --> 00:28:23,580
 our perspective narrows, and we only get stuck,

627
00:28:23,580 --> 00:28:25,820
 and we keep thinking about the thing we're wrestling with,

628
00:28:25,820 --> 00:28:27,980
 the thing that's right in front of us, and it's real.

629
00:28:27,980 --> 00:28:30,820
 And yes, it's something that we're walking through,

630
00:28:30,820 --> 00:28:34,060
 and it's a very personal experience.

631
00:28:34,060 --> 00:28:36,700
 But when our perspective tends to shrink,

632
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:39,280
 we get caught up in despair, and we forget, actually,

633
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,840
 God's ability, and His love, and His power

634
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:44,140
 goes beyond just answering the one prayer

635
00:28:44,140 --> 00:28:45,220
 that we're praying.

636
00:28:45,220 --> 00:28:49,140
 But He hears everybody, and He's still able to act.

637
00:28:49,140 --> 00:28:51,600
 His love and His power is infinite.

638
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:53,840
 So as this angel begins to tell Zachariah

639
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:55,480
 about his son, about John,

640
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:57,800
 and the type of man he's going to be,

641
00:28:57,800 --> 00:29:00,080
 something else becomes very clear.

642
00:29:00,080 --> 00:29:03,520
 John is not just gonna be an ordinary child.

643
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:05,480
 The angel starts saying things like,

644
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:09,720
 this man, this boy, he will be filled with the Holy Spirit

645
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,440
 even before he is born.

646
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:15,520
 We see this happening when Elizabeth goes to visit Mary.

647
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:18,440
 Remember the story of John is kicking, right,

648
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:22,280
 in Elizabeth's womb, because he knows

649
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:24,760
 the Holy Spirit has taught this infant

650
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:27,200
 in the womb of his mother that he is meeting

651
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:28,580
 the Messiah right now.

652
00:29:28,580 --> 00:29:32,880
 It tells us that many will rejoice at his birth.

653
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:35,680
 It tells us that he will bring back many

654
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:38,120
 of the people of Israel to the Lord their God.

655
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:41,940
 He will make ready a people prepared for the Lord.

656
00:29:41,940 --> 00:29:45,200
 You see, John was not just a child

657
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:48,200
 that Zachariah and Elizabeth had been praying for

658
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,680
 and waiting for.

659
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:51,720
 He's actually gonna be the fulfillment

660
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:53,760
 of these prophecies from long ago.

661
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:57,040
 He's the one that Isaiah says in his prophecy,

662
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:59,560
 the voice of one calling in the wilderness,

663
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:03,220
 prepare the way of the Lord, make straight a way

664
00:30:03,220 --> 00:30:05,100
 in the desert for our God.

665
00:30:05,100 --> 00:30:08,880
 So do you see what's happening, church?

666
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:12,560
 In answering the prayer of Zachariah and Elizabeth,

667
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:15,440
 in their longing for a child, God was actually using

668
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:17,800
 this opportunity for the bigger prayer

669
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:20,760
 and the bigger cry of the whole nation.

670
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:22,540
 Not just the whole nation, the whole world,

671
00:30:22,540 --> 00:30:26,760
 the redemption and the rescue of all people.

672
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:28,640
 Right, this is what we mean when God is able

673
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:31,640
 to do more than we can ask or imagine.

674
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,960
 This is so much more than just the promises

675
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:36,800
 of Zachariah and Elizabeth having a son at last.

676
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:41,120
 It's the fulfillment of the reality of God's promises

677
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:43,620
 for all people of all time.

678
00:30:43,620 --> 00:30:47,000
 This is God proving his love and telling us

679
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:49,080
 that the needs and the fears and the hopes

680
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:53,100
 of the people will certainly not go unanswered.

681
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:55,320
 That the prayers of the past 400 years

682
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:57,280
 have not fallen on deaf ears.

683
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:59,680
 The cry for a Messiah has been heard

684
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:01,780
 and I'm finally taking action.

685
00:31:01,780 --> 00:31:05,380
 Redemption is about to unfold before your very eyes.

686
00:31:05,380 --> 00:31:09,540
 This is me at work, paving the way for my son

687
00:31:09,540 --> 00:31:11,060
 to come into this world.

688
00:31:11,060 --> 00:31:16,600
 Which is why then Zachariah's response

689
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:20,500
 seems quite anti-climatic, right?

690
00:31:20,500 --> 00:31:23,240
 You would think that he would be celebrating

691
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:24,320
 the moment he heard this, right?

692
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:25,520
 An angel has appeared.

693
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:27,400
 He's told him the news, right?

694
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:28,960
 He would have known these stories

695
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:30,240
 of angels appearing in the past.

696
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,640
 He would have known the history,

697
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,520
 the cry of the many people.

698
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:36,560
 You think he'd run out praising everybody,

699
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:38,620
 telling everybody, look what God has done

700
00:31:38,620 --> 00:31:40,200
 and angels just came to me.

701
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:42,000
 You know, I'm mad to be a father

702
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:45,060
 and this boy is gonna prepare the way for the Messiah.

703
00:31:45,060 --> 00:31:50,140
 But instead, it seems as though

704
00:31:50,140 --> 00:31:54,240
 that his past disappointment has been too strong, right?

705
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:56,600
 And his doubts have clouded his ability

706
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:58,120
 to really trust in God,

707
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:01,200
 even if such a great sign has come to tell him.

708
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:04,400
 He questions, he asks the angel,

709
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:07,600
 how can I be sure of this?

710
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:12,560
 I am an old man and my wife is well along in years.

711
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:15,960
 And you know, when we read stories like that,

712
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:19,440
 it's easy for us to like judge a bit, Zachariah, at first.

713
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:21,680
 Like, come on, dude, like an angel,

714
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:23,520
 God's word, you're still doubting?

715
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:26,360
 And I feel for him, right?

716
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:29,640
 He's looking for a further sign, he needs more assurance.

717
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:33,800
 I'm not saying the way he responded was correct,

718
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:36,500
 but I can understand why he would be feeling this way.

719
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:40,180
 'Cause even as I look back on my own life,

720
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:43,680
 and maybe this is true for you as well,

721
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:47,720
 it does seem as though there have been many more times

722
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:51,360
 when prayers have gone unanswered

723
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:55,840
 than God giving me things that I've been praying for.

724
00:32:55,840 --> 00:33:00,700
 I've lost three of my good best friends to cancer,

725
00:33:00,700 --> 00:33:05,740
 even though every time I pray to God for healing,

726
00:33:05,740 --> 00:33:10,140
 I have prayed unceasingly for my own wrestle

727
00:33:10,140 --> 00:33:12,200
 with my own genetic condition, right?

728
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:14,620
 It's something I continue to wrestle with every day,

729
00:33:14,620 --> 00:33:17,020
 this literal thorn in the flesh

730
00:33:17,020 --> 00:33:18,520
 that I feel God's given to me.

731
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:22,280
 And every time I pray, God's response is,

732
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:24,180
 my grace is sufficient.

733
00:33:24,180 --> 00:33:27,040
 I prayed in great faith that my children

734
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:28,480
 would not inherit this disease,

735
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:31,960
 and yet here we are, a steady constant stream

736
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:35,820
 of hospital visits, of MRI scans to manage their condition.

737
00:33:35,820 --> 00:33:40,640
 And so as I said in the beginning,

738
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:42,200
 I and most of us in this room

739
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,800
 have gone through many seasons of life

740
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:47,160
 where we doubt God's goodness,

741
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:49,680
 where when we sing words like you have never let me down,

742
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:51,520
 like I really have to wrestle with myself,

743
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:53,160
 do I really mean those words, God?

744
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:55,760
 'Cause I feel like down sometimes, right?

745
00:33:55,760 --> 00:34:00,000
 Hear me when I say this, church.

746
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:05,420
 There is room and permission for doubt

747
00:34:05,420 --> 00:34:08,840
 in the journey of your relationship with Jesus.

748
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:13,040
 Just don't let that doubt control your life

749
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:14,980
 and lead you into a place of despair,

750
00:34:14,980 --> 00:34:18,680
 but instead, allow that doubt to lead you deeper

751
00:34:18,680 --> 00:34:21,360
 into faith in the Lord.

752
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:25,880
 And see, when we do this, faith and doubt

753
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:28,700
 can actually work hand in hand.

754
00:34:28,700 --> 00:34:33,240
 Maybe thinking about this this way might help.

755
00:34:33,240 --> 00:34:38,240
 Doubt is to faith as grief is to love, right?

756
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:40,800
 We love love.

757
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:43,680
 Love is a strong, powerful force.

758
00:34:43,680 --> 00:34:46,000
 Love can overcome all things.

759
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:49,240
 Love is the fuel of our relationships.

760
00:34:49,240 --> 00:34:52,600
 Think about all the things and people that you love,

761
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:55,640
 right, your spouse, your family, your friends,

762
00:34:55,640 --> 00:34:58,400
 your brothers and sisters in Christ,

763
00:34:58,400 --> 00:35:00,820
 ramen, your pets, right, whatever it is, right?

764
00:35:00,820 --> 00:35:03,320
 Love is this thing that fuels us

765
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:05,760
 and makes life worth living.

766
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:09,980
 Without love, life would be almost meaningless.

767
00:35:09,980 --> 00:35:11,320
 It would be no life at all.

768
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:16,320
 But alongside love is a shadow,

769
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:18,840
 the shadow of grief.

770
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:22,240
 Grief is this inevitable part of love, right?

771
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:24,520
 The two can coexist in this weird dance

772
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,000
 that they do with each other

773
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,360
 because to love someone is also to risk

774
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:30,800
 grieving them as well.

775
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:36,140
 And the same thing can be said about faith and doubt.

776
00:35:36,140 --> 00:35:39,280
 Right, without doubt, faith would be like

777
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:43,200
 a mathematical equation, right,

778
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:44,800
 or like a computer program.

779
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:46,900
 Do this and that's gonna happen.

780
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:50,440
 But faith isn't like that, right?

781
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:53,280
 Faith is this thing that apparently we can grow in

782
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,600
 and get stronger in.

783
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:57,320
 It's an active and living thing, right?

784
00:35:57,320 --> 00:36:00,320
 Which is why in order to have faith,

785
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:03,780
 we also have to have the ability to doubt.

786
00:36:03,780 --> 00:36:06,440
 If we never had to doubt anything,

787
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:08,440
 then what would be the need for faith?

788
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:13,200
 So we must wrestle without doubt.

789
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,920
 But like I said, we must be careful

790
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:16,800
 not to let doubts prevail

791
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:20,140
 and sit upon the throne of our hearts.

792
00:36:20,140 --> 00:36:22,080
 'Cause when doubt sits on the throne of our heart,

793
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:23,640
 it becomes an idol.

794
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:27,200
 And we start to believe things like,

795
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:28,440
 I know better than God.

796
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:31,080
 I don't need God anymore.

797
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:33,120
 When throne sits on our hearts,

798
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:34,920
 we start believing in his power.

799
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:37,880
 Even Jesus said this himself,

800
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:40,920
 that in his own town, he could not do many miracles

801
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:45,000
 because they doubted, because of the lack of faith.

802
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:49,880
 So I'm gonna give us three things that we can do

803
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:52,780
 to guide us in our doubts.

804
00:36:52,780 --> 00:36:55,400
 These three things will hopefully help you

805
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:57,720
 as you go in these seasons of doubt

806
00:36:57,720 --> 00:37:00,320
 and wrestling with unanswered prayer

807
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:03,600
 and the unsureness that we feel in our lives sometimes.

808
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:05,280
 Hopefully you can use these things

809
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:08,400
 and the things we talked about just now to guide us through.

810
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:10,780
 Number one is this.

811
00:37:10,780 --> 00:37:13,620
 Turn your doubt into a prayer.

812
00:37:13,620 --> 00:37:16,340
 Turn your doubt into a prayer.

813
00:37:16,340 --> 00:37:18,920
 See, when we look at the life of Jesus,

814
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:21,400
 this is exactly how he handles his doubt.

815
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:25,200
 Yes, church, even Jesus,

816
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:29,400
 who is described as the author and perfecter of our faith,

817
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:32,800
 whilst he was on this earth, had his moments of doubt.

818
00:37:34,020 --> 00:37:35,700
 When Jesus was in the wilderness,

819
00:37:35,700 --> 00:37:38,360
 fasting and praying for 40 days and 40 nights,

820
00:37:38,360 --> 00:37:40,200
 and then the enemy comes,

821
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:44,400
 he tries to use the same tactics that he did with Eve.

822
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:48,360
 He tries to use doubt to get Jesus to trust him

823
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:51,220
 rather than his father's plans for him.

824
00:37:51,220 --> 00:37:54,880
 But Jesus passes that test,

825
00:37:54,880 --> 00:37:58,040
 and he comes through standing strong in his faith,

826
00:37:58,040 --> 00:38:00,440
 standing strong in the word of God.

827
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:03,720
 And Jesus had to fight back against him, though, right?

828
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,580
 And again, in the garden of Gethsemane,

829
00:38:05,580 --> 00:38:07,460
 when he was about to go to the cross,

830
00:38:07,460 --> 00:38:10,500
 he prays, he cries out to God,

831
00:38:10,500 --> 00:38:14,080
 "My father, if there's any other possible way,

832
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:17,100
 "may this cup be taken from me,

833
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:21,360
 "but not my will, your will."

834
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:24,340
 Right, he wrestled with that.

835
00:38:24,340 --> 00:38:26,060
 He said, "If there's any other way,

836
00:38:26,060 --> 00:38:28,200
 "I would much rather do that, Lord,

837
00:38:28,200 --> 00:38:31,880
 "but still I'm gonna submit to you."

838
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:35,220
 And even as he's on the cross, Jesus cries out,

839
00:38:35,220 --> 00:38:39,800
 "My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?"

840
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:45,620
 It's painful, but yet somehow beautiful and vulnerable

841
00:38:45,620 --> 00:38:46,780
 what Jesus does here.

842
00:38:46,780 --> 00:38:51,620
 Each time, he fully acknowledges his pain and his doubts,

843
00:38:51,620 --> 00:38:54,280
 the things that he's wrestling with,

844
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:59,120
 and yet he still chooses to cry out to God in prayer.

845
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:01,040
 He still chooses trust.

846
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:03,040
 He still chooses obedience.

847
00:39:03,040 --> 00:39:07,800
 He still stands firm on God's word till the very end.

848
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:14,720
 He turns his doubt into a cry of prayer to God.

849
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:18,640
 That's what I encourage us today.

850
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:20,880
 Turn your doubt into a prayer.

851
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,880
 Whatever it is that you're struggling with,

852
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:25,640
 bring it to the Lord, like we see in the Psalms.

853
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:28,880
 How, when, why, how long?

854
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:33,120
 But bring them before God and ask him,

855
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:36,980
 ask him to handle it.

856
00:39:36,980 --> 00:39:41,840
 As we do this, we're acknowledging

857
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:44,800
 that his ways are not our ways,

858
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:48,420
 and we trust that even as we hold on,

859
00:39:48,420 --> 00:39:50,860
 we will see his goodness.

860
00:39:50,860 --> 00:39:54,500
 We trust that even as we wrestle with our doubts,

861
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:58,820
 he proves that time and time again, he is faithful.

862
00:39:59,780 --> 00:40:02,020
 He is able to bring us through,

863
00:40:02,020 --> 00:40:04,340
 and maybe it's not in a way that we expected,

864
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:06,820
 but he is there for us.

865
00:40:06,820 --> 00:40:09,660
 So we turn our doubt into a prayer.

866
00:40:09,660 --> 00:40:15,020
 Number two is this, sit in silence.

867
00:40:15,020 --> 00:40:18,420
 When Zechariah makes his doubts known to God,

868
00:40:18,420 --> 00:40:21,860
 for a moment, God turns him mute.

869
00:40:21,860 --> 00:40:25,860
 Now, on the surface, it seems like it's a punishment,

870
00:40:25,860 --> 00:40:28,460
 but actually, it's not a punishment, I don't think.

871
00:40:28,460 --> 00:40:30,260
 Or if it is a punishment,

872
00:40:30,260 --> 00:40:33,740
 it's like a punishment from grace,

873
00:40:33,740 --> 00:40:35,660
 'cause this is God trying to get Zechariah

874
00:40:35,660 --> 00:40:38,940
 to surrender himself,

875
00:40:38,940 --> 00:40:43,700
 just to sit in the silence for a minute.

876
00:40:43,700 --> 00:40:48,460
 And it's only sometimes when we turn off all the noise,

877
00:40:48,460 --> 00:40:51,020
 when we make room and sit in the silence

878
00:40:51,020 --> 00:40:54,300
 and wait for God to speak,

879
00:40:54,300 --> 00:40:57,820
 that somehow in that space, we hear his voice again.

880
00:40:57,820 --> 00:40:59,100
 Somehow in that space,

881
00:40:59,100 --> 00:41:02,540
 our faith is being slowly built back up.

882
00:41:02,540 --> 00:41:05,720
 And through silence, we're reminded

883
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:08,940
 of how God has been there for us in the past,

884
00:41:08,940 --> 00:41:12,700
 and our promises to us will never, ever fail.

885
00:41:12,700 --> 00:41:18,620
 So we sit in silence and wait for God to speak.

886
00:41:18,620 --> 00:41:23,920
 And number three is this, we remember God's word.

887
00:41:24,940 --> 00:41:28,100
 Zechariah was a man who knew God's word well.

888
00:41:28,100 --> 00:41:29,460
 He would've remembered that,

889
00:41:29,460 --> 00:41:31,060
 actually, this isn't the first time

890
00:41:31,060 --> 00:41:32,740
 that God has promised an elderly couple

891
00:41:32,740 --> 00:41:34,500
 that they would have children.

892
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:37,820
 He would remember the story of Abraham and Sarah,

893
00:41:37,820 --> 00:41:39,520
 how they were also past the age

894
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:41,620
 when they should've been able to have children,

895
00:41:41,620 --> 00:41:43,620
 and yet, God promised them

896
00:41:43,620 --> 00:41:45,820
 that they would have as many offspring

897
00:41:45,820 --> 00:41:48,300
 as there are stars in the sky.

898
00:41:48,300 --> 00:41:51,620
 And here they were today, a line of priestly family,

899
00:41:51,620 --> 00:41:53,220
 all the way, tracing the lineage,

900
00:41:53,220 --> 00:41:55,780
 all the way back to Abraham and Sarah,

901
00:41:55,780 --> 00:42:01,920
 living examples of God's promise to Abraham and Sarah

902
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,620
 to where they were today.

903
00:42:03,620 --> 00:42:06,640
 Could God do it again?

904
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:09,200
 Yes and amen.

905
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:12,980
 By remembering what God has done in the past

906
00:42:12,980 --> 00:42:16,560
 through His word, it helps us to believe

907
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:19,540
 that God is able and acts to fulfill

908
00:42:19,540 --> 00:42:22,980
 His promises in the present.

909
00:42:22,980 --> 00:42:27,000
 Even if it might be ways that are surprising to us.

910
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:30,900
 So remember God's word.

911
00:42:30,900 --> 00:42:32,020
 Hold on to it.

912
00:42:32,020 --> 00:42:34,860
 Look back in scripture and see how good

913
00:42:34,860 --> 00:42:37,140
 God has been to us in the past.

914
00:42:37,140 --> 00:42:38,940
 And remember those promises.

915
00:42:38,940 --> 00:42:44,600
 And my prayer for us this morning is this, church,

916
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:45,900
 that in the end, I pray,

917
00:42:45,900 --> 00:42:50,940
 even in our doubts, we can continue to praise.

918
00:42:50,940 --> 00:42:54,360
 Even in the end, Zechariah ends his story

919
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:57,500
 by saying, "Praise be to the Lord, the God of Israel,

920
00:42:57,500 --> 00:43:01,520
 "because He has come to His people and redeemed them."

921
00:43:01,520 --> 00:43:04,460
 So this morning, church,

922
00:43:04,460 --> 00:43:07,060
 I too want to end our time in prayer.

923
00:43:07,060 --> 00:43:11,160
 Maybe you just wanna make yourself comfortable

924
00:43:11,160 --> 00:43:13,260
 and close your eyes right now.

925
00:43:14,220 --> 00:43:16,980
 (pages rustling)

926
00:43:16,980 --> 00:43:27,300
 And we have many people here listening,

927
00:43:27,300 --> 00:43:28,760
 and online as well.

928
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:35,740
 I know what some of you might be going through,

929
00:43:35,740 --> 00:43:38,860
 but there's a whole lot of wrestling

930
00:43:38,860 --> 00:43:40,020
 in this room right now.

931
00:43:42,060 --> 00:43:44,900
 Lots of shadows of doubt that are looming over us.

932
00:43:44,900 --> 00:43:50,100
 I don't know exactly what that is,

933
00:43:50,100 --> 00:43:54,660
 but what I do know is God is okay with your doubts.

934
00:43:54,660 --> 00:44:04,460
 And He's okay as we bring our prayer before Him.

935
00:44:04,460 --> 00:44:11,560
 For what He doesn't want is for us to stay there.

936
00:44:11,560 --> 00:44:14,320
 (pages rustling)

937
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:20,840
 And so right now, whatever doubt

938
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:22,080
 that you are wrestling with, church,

939
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:24,680
 I encourage you just to bring it before the Lord

940
00:44:24,680 --> 00:44:25,520
 into a prayer.

941
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:28,520
 Question and ask Him.

942
00:44:28,520 --> 00:44:30,460
 Talk to Him.

943
00:44:30,460 --> 00:44:34,440
 (pages rustling)

944
00:44:35,440 --> 00:44:38,020
 (gentle music)

945
00:44:38,020 --> 00:44:45,800
 And as you bring it before Him, to Him in prayer,

946
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:49,480
 after you've done that, just sit back

947
00:44:49,480 --> 00:44:53,920
 and be comfortable with the silence

948
00:44:53,920 --> 00:44:55,240
 that may follow that time.

949
00:44:55,240 --> 00:45:03,120
 And as we quieten our hearts and our minds,

950
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:06,320
 open them up then to hear what God has to say

951
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:08,360
 about that situation,

952
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:10,520
 that prayer that you've just brought to Him.

953
00:45:10,520 --> 00:45:19,380
 Allow the Holy Spirit just to come and minister to you.

954
00:45:31,720 --> 00:45:34,480
 And if you need reminders, open up God's Word

955
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:36,400
 and turn to it.

956
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:42,240
 Look back in the stories, look back in the situations

957
00:45:42,240 --> 00:45:47,080
 where God has come through for His people.

958
00:45:47,080 --> 00:45:55,660
 And we plant our faith, we build our foundation

959
00:45:55,660 --> 00:45:58,260
 in the Word of God.

960
00:45:58,260 --> 00:46:00,840
 (gentle music)

961
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:05,300
 And so Jesus, we ask that you would come meet us

962
00:46:05,300 --> 00:46:09,780
 in our doubts, in our wrestling, in our unsureness.

963
00:46:09,780 --> 00:46:19,540
 Lord, and I pray that we do pray in faith

964
00:46:19,540 --> 00:46:20,740
 for prayers to be answered.

965
00:46:20,740 --> 00:46:23,860
 We do pray in faith for the breakthroughs that we are

966
00:46:23,860 --> 00:46:27,180
 that are being lifted up to you right now to become reality.

967
00:46:28,180 --> 00:46:30,780
 (gentle music)

968
00:46:30,780 --> 00:46:34,200
 But more than that, Lord, we hold on to our faith in you,

969
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:38,740
 our trust in you, our surrender to you.

970
00:46:38,740 --> 00:46:47,340
 To know that you are working and doing things

971
00:46:47,340 --> 00:46:49,560
 on our behalf that we might not even see.

972
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:54,300
 That you are a good God.

973
00:46:54,460 --> 00:46:57,040
 (gentle music)

974
00:46:57,040 --> 00:46:59,840
 Who loves us.

975
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:04,460
 And so Jesus, meet us in our doubts.

976
00:47:04,460 --> 00:47:07,620
 Help us to cry out to you and you alone

977
00:47:07,620 --> 00:47:11,460
 and through our doubts, Father, may you draw us closer

978
00:47:11,460 --> 00:47:14,360
 in faith, in love, in relationship to you, Jesus.

979
00:47:14,360 --> 00:47:16,980
 In your name we pray.

